The paper deals with the problem of directed spanners, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The main technique used in the paper is flow-based linear programming relaxations, which is a common tool in optimization and numerical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves some combinatorial and probabilistic arguments, which suggest the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible choices.
